ething affecting the nerves in that area.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041718,0.092831,0.10325,0.12419,0.097393,0.09133,0.088982,0.084689,0.079653,0.073356,0.065235,0.057366],"unified_progress":[0.038022,0.075105,0.097511,0.10984,0.10417,0.10012,0.10008,0.093225,0.090243,0.080017,0.065197,0.046467]},{"section":8,"text":"The left-sided Horner's syndrome adds another clue.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039662,0.077059,0.094643,0.10472,0.10287,0.099022,0.096664,0.091001,0.085195,0.078979,0.070192,0.060001],"unified_progress":[0.038647,0.070443,0.086394,0.0964,0.10142,0.099775,0.099877,0.097893,0.093734,0.088194,0.072961,0.054264]},{"section":9,"text":"Horner's syndrome involves ipsilateral ptosis, miosis, and anhidrosis, which is caused by a lesion in the sympathetic nervous system pathway, typically in the neck or upper chest.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03369,0.062313,0.080938,0.092399,0.10032,0.10248,0.10607,0.10293,0.097096,0.086237,0.074561,0.060972],"unified_progress":[0.0364,0.067134,0.086042,0.097301,0.1036,0.10677,0.10277,0.098771,0.09641,0.084139,0.068909,0.051751]},{"section":10,"text":"Putting this together, the patient likely has a tumor that's affecting both the lungs and the sympathetic chain.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041188,0.069138,0.076972,0.082735,0.087408,0.089417,0.091381,0.091486,0.090034,0.094447,0.091226,0.094567],"unified_progress":[0.038942,0.065978,0.076719,0.086066,0.089862,0.093409,0.093417,0.093839,0.093546,0.089995,0.089061,0.089167]},{"section":11,"text":"Since he's a smoker, the most common primary tumor would be small cell lung cancer.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045148,0.071195,0.073451,0.076801,0.082331,0.08541,0.089922,0.092207,0.09307,0.096334,0.095836,0.098295],"unified_progress":[0.044746,0.066854,0.072901,0.078917,0.082657,0.088388,0.